&lt;p&gt;The Wimbledon Championship:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Wimbledon Championship&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;oldest Lawn Tennis tournament&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;in the&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;This tournament is the only&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;tournament&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;that is played on the&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Grass Court&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;instead of&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Turf or Clay Court and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;it is played in a&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;round-robin&amp;nbsp;format.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Championship&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;was started on&amp;nbsp;9th July&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;1877.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is hosted in&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;London (England) every year.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This is one of the&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;four Grand Slams Tournament of Lawn Tennis.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Other&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Three Grand Slams of Lawn Tennis are (Australian Open, French Open, and The USA Open).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Wimbledon tournament&amp;nbsp;traditionally took place in&amp;nbsp;London&amp;nbsp;over&amp;nbsp;two weeks in late June and early July&amp;nbsp;every year, starting on the last&amp;nbsp;Monday in June&amp;nbsp;and culminating with the&amp;nbsp;Men&amp;#39;s Singles and&amp;nbsp;Women&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;Finals on the same day.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;inaugural tournament of Wimbledon&amp;nbsp;was&amp;nbsp;won, by Spencer Gore.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;Matches of the tournament&amp;nbsp;in the&amp;nbsp;Men&amp;#39;s Singles and Men&amp;#39;s Doubles are best-of-five sets and the rest of&amp;nbsp;all other events are best-of-three sets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

